---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Goddamn Apps">
  <article class="case-page">
    <header class="case-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">Method</p>
      <h1>Mean name, sober receipts.</h1>
      <p class="summary">
        Goddamn Apps tracks consumer-hostile software behavior. The joke stops
        at the domain; the records should be sourced, specific, and easy to correct.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>What belongs here</h2>
      <p>
        Privacy abuse, malware-like behavior, dark patterns, subscription traps,
        refund obstruction, ad abuse, account hostage tactics, and price games.
      </p>

      <h2>How cases are written</h2>
      <p>
        Each record should say what happened, why it harms users, what evidence
        supports it, and whether the issue is reported, confirmed, fixed, or unresolved.
      </p>

      <h2>Send tips</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:tips@goddamnapps.com">tips@goddamnapps.com</a> with
        source links, screenshots, app versions, dates, device details, and reproduction
        notes when possible.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

